'''Third Person View''' is a desktop feature, temporarily exclusive to [[VRC+|VRC+]] until the end of June 2026 (expected), that allows users to switch their perspective from their avatar's point of view to a zoomed-out view.

== Controls ==
When enabled, users can adjust the distance from their avatar and switch between behind-the-back view and free rotation.
{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Button !! Description
|-
| '''F5'''|| ''Toggles Third Person View''
|-
| '''Scrollwheel'''|| ''Adjusts the distance from the avatar''
|-
| '''TAB'''|| ''Enabled free rotate mode''
|}

== Settings ==
The following settings can be adjusted in ''Main Menu -> Settings -> Graphics''.
{| class="wikitable"
|+
!Name
!Tooltip
|-
|'''Third Person View'''
|''See VRChat from behind your avatar! Toggle with F5, freely rotate with TAB, and adjust distance using mouse-wheel.''
|-
|'''Third Person View Distance'''
|''Sets the maximum distance the third person viewpoint can extend away from your avatar when third person view is active''
|-
|'''Third Person View Vertical'''
|''Sets the left/right position for the third person viewpoint relative to your avatar''
|}